						<summary>

						<p>Madanagōpālasvāmin Temple-Central Shrine, south wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanachakravartti Kōnērinmaikoṇḍān (Sundara-pāṇḍya ?) Year 9, day 156.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records an order of the king to the <hi rend="italic">nāṭṭār</hi> of Vēmbār-nāḍu stipulating that from <hi rend="italic">vāra-ppaṟṟu</hi> (lands under <hi rend="italic">vāram</hi> tenure) <hi rend="italic">vāram</hi> may be collected and from <hi rend="italic">kaḍamai-ppaṟṟu</hi> (lands which paid <hi rend="italic">kaḍamai</hi>) <hi rend="italic">kaḍamai</hi> may be collected. The proceeds of the collection <hi rend="italic">(mudal)</hi> will be utilised for meeting the expenses <hi rend="italic">(chelav-iṟukka)</hi> of royal officials (Sundara-pāṇḍiya-dēvarkāriyañ-cheyvār).</p>						

						</summary>
